# Cursor AI Rules for irsal-notes

## 1. Engineering Approach
- Think like a lead engineer: be smart, thoughtful, and consider best practices
- Consider edge cases, performance implications, and maintainability
- Write clean, well-structured code that follows established patterns
- Think about the broader context and how changes affect the system

## 2. CSS Module Class Name Access
- Always use bracket notation for CSS module class names
- ✅ Correct: `className={styles['panel']}`
- ❌ Incorrect: `className={styles.panel}`
- ✅ Correct: `className={styles.panel-container}`
- ❌ Incorrect: `className={styles['panelContainer']}`
- This applies to all CSS module imports (`.module.scss`, `.module.css`)

## 3. SCSS Nesting
- Always use SCSS nesting syntax instead of flat CSS
- ✅ Correct:
  ```scss
  .container {
    display: flex;
    
    .item {
      padding: 1rem;
      
      &:hover {
        background: blue;
      }
    }
  }
  ```
- ❌ Incorrect:
  ```scss
  .container {
    display: flex;
  }
  .container .item {
    padding: 1rem;
  }
  .container .item:hover {
    background: blue;
  }
  ```
- Prefer nested selectors for better organization and readability

